Can we plant a native tree or plant for every SG family to call our own, and to help combat the very real climate crisis? That would be an amazing, meaningful gift for all Singaporeans (and our wildlife) this NDP, one that will last for generations and generations to come. With global pandemic crisis, clinate change crisis, biodiversity loss crisis, etc (disaster list goes on), we need to really start thinking and living Sustainably. We need to wean ourselves away from the throwaway and gimme free stuff culture. As a national issue, we are running out of space to put our waste. We need to focus our precious resources on critical stuff. Once a upon a time we did not have funpacks but still enjoyed ourselves at NDP, even in the rain. If we think creatively, we can have a more meaningful and fun NDP tradition that is sustainable. So no funpack for me please, I choose to plant a tree!
